                    If you are a resident of the European Economic Area (EEA) or
                    Spain, you have certain data protection rights under GDPR
                    and Spanish law, including:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                    <li>
                        The right to access, update or delete the information we
                        have on you.
                    </li>
                    <li>The right of rectification.</li>
                    <li>The right to object.</li>
                    <li>The right of restriction.</li>
                    <li>The right to data portability.</li>
                    <li>The right to withdraw consent.</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-text-muted">
                    Please note that we may ask you to verify your identity
                    before responding to such requests.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3 mt-6">
                    7. Children's Privacy
                </h2>
                <p>
                    Our Service is not directed to children under 13. We do not
